<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Washington Naval Arms Conference achieved:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Military alliance formation</option>
            <option letter="b">Naval arms limitations among major powers</option>
            <option letter="c">Increased naval spending</option>
            <option letter="d">Colonial expansion agreements</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Washington Naval Conference (1921-1922) achieved significant naval arms limitations through the Five-Power Treaty, which established a 5:5:3:1.75:1.75 ratio of naval strength between the United States, Britain, Japan, France, and Italy respectively. This agreement successfully limited naval armaments among major powers and reduced military spending, representing a significant diplomatic effort to prevent a naval arms race.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
